      "message": "sscanf won\u0027t work for reasons unrelated to whether we use if/switch or 1 or 4 functions.\n\nre switch vs if: i prefer switch in places where we handle distinct cases/scenarios, and this is a perfect example\n\nre 1 vs 4 functions: i think 1 public function is simpler than 4 functions and yet it is convenient-enough to use, even if we know exactly the type of buildset we are expecting to parse\n  c, _ :\u003d buildbucket.ParseBuildSet(s).(*buildbucket.GitilesCommit)\n  if c \u003d\u003d nil {\n    // handle error\n  }\nIf I make a function per type, in each of them I\u0027d have to do prefix checking (again), string splitting, checking of component number, checking for empty path components. I think it would be more complex. \n\nWDYT?",
